		<title>The Importance of Controlling Trade Show Rental Costs</title>
		<link>http://insightsintomarketing.com/marketing/the-importance-of-controlling-trade-show-rental-costs</link>
		<comments>http://insightsintomarketing.com/marketing/the-importance-of-controlling-trade-show-rental-costs#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 29 May 2012 20:18:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Mark Delacruz</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[marketing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[branding]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[custom displays]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[display]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[exhibit]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[exhibition]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[exhibitions]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[exhibits]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[rental displays]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://insightsintomarketing.com/marketing/the-importance-of-controlling-trade-show-rental-costs</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Your company can suffer from going overboard with trade show exhibits costs. Your company will tend to overspend if you do not have clear goals on how you would like your display exhibit to be. Here are some ways to lessen costs in trade shows:]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Your company can suffer from going overboard with trade show exhibits costs. Your company will tend to overspend if you do not have clear goals on how you would like your display exhibit to be. Here are some ways to lessen costs in trade shows:</p>
<p>*	Prepare in advance</p>
<p>]*	Use portable displays</p>
<p>*	Use rentals</p>
<p>*	Upgrade current exhibits</p>
<p>*	Buy a second hand display unit</p>
<p>*	Set up your booth in advance</p>
<p>*	Get familiar with exhibition ground services</p>
<p>*	Keep emergency materials handy</p>
<p>In order for your company to save in marketing costs, do not participate in every trade show that is being held for the year. Check out the reputation of the organizers first before deciding in participating in one. Trade shows organized poorly may be a waste of time and money if you are going to participate in one. If there are a lot of trade shows being held per year, you should choose only a few to participate in. By doing this, you can easily plan in advance your marketing strategy and plan what your trade show display will look like. Planning in advance will allow you to lessen costs because you will be able to canvass different suppliers and printers for your brochures, posters, and other printed literature.</p>
<p>If you plan to take your own exhibits to the show, then use lightweight portable, table top, pop-up or modular displays. This reduces freight and storage costs. Items can be easily packed, unpacked and set up at the venue. By having modular units that are flexible, you can check out your booth space and use displays that fit in comfortably. Extra fittings can be easily stored or used depending on available space. Another good option is to consider using a display rental instead of investing in one.</p>
<p>For small companies or companies with limited budget, it is best that they start participating in trade shows by renting display booths rather than having one built for them. This is especially practical for companies that plan to attend only one trade exhibit a year. When planning to rent, make sure that the rental company is located within or at least near the city where the event is going to take place. This will save on transport cost and you will be assured that the rental company is already familiar with the venue.</p>
<p>If you already have display units and exhibits and they look worn out or they have been used several times, you can consider upgrading them instead of investing in new ones. By redesigning the basic structure, re-laminating panels or changing the graphics, you spend a small amount and have a fresh and trendy looking booth. A pre-owned display exhibit is another great cost-cutting option. Many large corporations with unlimited marketing budgets keep changing their display booths very often and sell of their old units.</p>
<p>A pre-owned unit will quickly and inexpensively look as good as new with paint retouching or wall panel replacing. Adding backlighting and redesigning the graphics will work wonders in advertising your company&#8217;s products and services. Nowadays, there are a variety of techniques and designs that can save you on your construction time and cost.</p>
<p>If the schedule of the trade show is going to be on a weekday, then you must avoid the rush during the weekends by pre-planning how you are going to assemble your display booth in advanced. Extra costs can also be avoided with advanced planning. Also, if there are any glitches observed, they can be ironed out before the opening of the exhibit. Advanced knowledge of the place where the exhibit will be held will allow you to be familiar with all the materials that you will need to bring such as power cords and additional tables and chairs.</p>
<p>Strategic location of a booth display plays and important role in attracting maximum foot traffic. So, planning in advance reduces costs and improves traffic too. Finally, make sure you have a small handy kit bag with emergency supplies. This could include extra power cords for the computer, extra giveaways, promotional pamphlets, scissors, tools, paper, pens, Velcro, sticky tape etc. Careful thought and planning ahead are keys to successful trade show participation at minimum cost.</p>
